channel.title: Interleaved RSS Feed
channel.description: This is an interleaved feed of the most recent entries from each RSS source, skipping any feeds with errors.

item.title: Over the Line: Georgia Rep. Collins Posts Tasteless Tweet Mocking RFK Jr. Over Family's Assassinations
Barron Trump to enter politics as Florida delegate at GOP convention
item.description: Barron Trump, the youngest child of former President Trump will enter the political fray for the first time when he will be an at-large delegate to the Republican National Convention.

item.title: Barron Trump, 18, to Make Political Debut
item.description: Former President Donald Trump's youngest son, Barron Trump, has been chosen to serve as a Florida delegate to the Republican National Convention, the state party chairman said Wednesday.

item.title: Biden's Comment About Trump in Burnett Interview Has Everyone Talking About Dems and 'Small Ds'
Alabama lawmakers strengthen penalties for falsely reporting a crime after Carlee Russell kidnapping hoax
item.description: Falsely reporting a crime to law enforcement is one step away from becoming a felony in certain circumstances in Alabama after the bill passed the state legislature on Wednesday.

item.title: Sen. Paul to Newsmax: Biden Immigration Policies Led to Tragic Murder
item.description: In a scathing rebuke of the Biden administration's immigration policies, Sen. Rand Paul, R-Ky., asserted that the recent murder of nursing student Laken Riley should be enough for Americans to reject the administration's approach.

item.title: Joe Biden's Insane Interview With Erin Burnett Should Be the Final Straw for American Voters
Biden national security adviser's wife launches run for House seat in key swing state
item.description: Maggie Goodlander, a former top Biden administration official and the wife of National Security Adviser Jake Sullivan, launches a Democratic congressional campaign in battleground New Hampshire

item.title: British MP Lammy to Newsmax: UK Can Work With Trump If He Wins
item.description: David Lammy, Britain's Shadow Foreign Secretary, told Newsmax on Wednesday that although he has been a critic of Donald Trump, he is confident his country can work with the former president should he prevail in November's election.

item.title: WATCH: Gutfeld Mocks Kristi Noem Over Show Cancelation, Hilariously 'Interviews' Dana as Noem, Instead
FIRST ON FOX: Biden gets boost from major health care group warning Trump poses 'threat to public health'
item.description: A group of 48 former high-level medical officials have penned a letter pleading with Americans not to put former President Trump back in the White House.

item.title: FDA Chief Tells Senate Agency Is Preparing for Bird Flu Mutation
item.description: The Food and Drug Administration (FDA) informed legislators on Wednesday that the agency is making preparatory measures in case the current avian flu is able to mutate and transmit to humans on a massive scale.

item.title: Biden Gets Busted on Big Lie in Wisconsin With New, Ridiculous Tall Tale
Ohio AG defends letter warning 'woke' masked anti-Israel protesters they face prison time: 'We have a society'
item.description: Ohio's Republican Attorney General is pushing back against 'woke' critics of his recent letter reminding anti-Israel protesters of a law that could mean prison time.

item.title: Israeli Amb Slams Dem Accusations of Withholding Aid to Gaza
item.description: Israel's ambassador to the United States, Michael Herzog, has strongly rebuked nearly 90 lawmakers for accusing Israel of purposefully withholding humanitarian aid from Gaza's 2.2 million Palestinians, Politico reported.
